# Claude Code Rules

## Style Preferences
- No emojis in any files
- Write documentation that sounds like a human wrote it
- Keep things concise and practical
- Focus on what matters, skip the fluff

## Commit Practices
- Make commits after each logical piece of work
- Write clear, descriptive commit messages
- Don't batch unrelated changes

## General
- Don't include server-specific information in documentation
- Keep README focused on setup and usage
